frameDefinitions: This frame contains nouns denoting a rank or level within an established hierarchy.
An Entity is rated as unexpected for its context in terms of its magnitude.
A System is perceived as complex depending on the intricacy of the interconnectivty of its parts or components.
An Agent behaves as if they were a particular individual or type of Simulated_entity with the intent of misleading observers of their behavior.
Item-1 and Item-2 are compatible with each other if they can exist or function together in some context without problems, conflict, or other undesirable situation.
An Experiencer has an easy or difficult time carrying out an Activity.
frameExamples: The <t>entire</t> apple was riddled with worms .
San Diego freeways are a <t>complex</t> array of poorly maintained roads.
The belfast bank robbers <t>posed</t> as police.
Make sure your site is <t>compatible</t> with any browser.
listRoleDefinitions: The Rank itself, usually denoted by the noun.
An entity which holds a particular <fen>Rank</fen>.
The item which is described in terms of its expectedness in the context.
The complete entity or system whose complexity is under consideration.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person who acts in a misleading way to create the impression that they are a particular individual or type of <fen>Simulated_entity</fen>.
The type or individual that the <fen>Agent</fen> gives the impression of being.
The time at which the <fen>Agent</fen> impersonates the <fen>Simulated_entity</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> gives the impression that they are the <fen>Simulated_entity</fen>.
The Frame Element <fen>Item_1</fen> marks the grammatically more prominent of the two entities, i.e.the subject in active clauses, when they are expressed separately.
The Frame Element <fen>Item_2</fen> marks the grammatically less prominent of the <fen>Items</fen> when they are expressed separately.
This role is used when the <fen>Items</fen> are expressed jointly in a phrase, either a plural or a coordinated NP.
This Frame Element is used for expressions that indicate a <fen>Parameter</fen> or respect in which the <fen>Items</fen> are said to be compatible, not in conflict.

This Frame Element marks expressions indicating the <fen>Activity</fen> that the <fen>Experiencer</fen> finds difficult or easy. In many cases, the relevant <fen>Activity</fen> has to be inferred from the context.
This Frame Element marks expressions that indicate which person judges carrying out the <fen>Activity</fen> to be easy or difficult.
The time at which the <fen>Activity</fen> takes place.
listRoleExamples: The entire <fex>day</fex> was spent on the project .
<fex>That technology</fex> turned out not to be compatible with the existing devices
My computer is not compatible <fex>with my new printer</fex>.
The two applications are compatible <fex>in their essential features</fex>.
The geology question on the exam was hard <fex>for me</fex>.
